The Mine Equipment Review Panel shall be composed of the following members, who shall be appointed by the commissioner not less than thirty (30) days after July 12, 2006:
One (1) member shall represent the National Institute of Occupational Safety and Health;
One (1) member shall represent the federal Mine Safety and Health Administration;
One (1) member shall represent the coal industry;
One (1) member shall be appointed from the membership of the United Mine Workers of America and shall represent mine labor, preferably a member of a Kentucky mine rescue team;
One (1) member shall represent the Department of Mining Engineering at the University of Kentucky; and
One (1) member shall be the director of the division.
